rd.  Jewish Chaim, Amrom, Amron, Aron, Arie, Cheskel, Eitan, Elchonon, Hersch, Mayer, Mendel.","German (<b>Grünwald</b>): habitational name from any of various places called Grün(e)wald, from Middle High German <i>grūene</i> ‘green’ + <i>walt</i> ‘wood, forest’. Compare   Greenwaldt  ,   Greenwalt  ,   Greenwood  , and   Gruenwald  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic; <b>Grünwald</b>): artificial name, with the same meaning as 1 above."]},{"name":"Greenwade","meanings":["Perhaps an altered form of English   Greenwood  ."]}]},{"name":"Cybbell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Cabell  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cabell","meanings":["Irish: Cab, the mouth, and allie, from aill, a cliff, signifying the mouth of a cliff"]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705206,"age":1,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1705207,"age":15,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1705210,"age":30,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1705212,"age":50,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1705213,"age":72,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1705216,"age":118,"year":"1688","toYear":"1689","julianDay":2337590,"title":"Glorious Revolution","description":"The Glorious Revolution brought the downfall of Catholic King James II and the reign of his Protestant daughter Mary and her Dutch husband, William III of Orange.","url":"http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/british/civil_war_revolution/glorious_revolution_01.shtml","urlTitle":"BBC - Glorious Revolution","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"When Cybbell Greenwood was born on 27 April 1569, in Ovenden, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Richard Greenwood, was 33 and her mother, Alice Kempe, was 29. She married Thomas Bradley on 27 July 1589. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"17 Apr 1569–":"27. aprill 1569–Surnud","1569–Femal